						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone (No. 1) set up near the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>Tailapa II [A.D. 981].</p>						

						<p>This inscription belonging to the reign of Tailapa is dated Śaka 903, Vishuva, Vaiśākha [śu.] 10, Thursday, Uttarā. The intended date may be A.D. 981, April 16, Saturday, and Uttarā nakshatra [star].</p>						

						<p>It states that Chavaṭṭoyya died and his son Chāmuṇḍa set up the memorial stone when Eṟagāri was holding the office of the <hi rend="italic">Nāḷ-gāmuṇḍa</hi> and Eṟechaṭṭa was holding the office of <hi rend="italic">Urgāmuṇḍa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
